This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the segmentation of retinal vessels, which is a common task in computer vision. The use of deep convolutional generative adversarial networks also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The introduction of the residual module for residual learning indicates that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the verification of the method on datasets suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
